<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS SIGN BACKUP QUARTERBACK
</HEADLINE>
 SIGNING-TEX (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ The Dallas Cowboys signed free-agent Jim Miller
to a one-year, $300,000 deal as their No. 3 quarterback, his agent
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Team owner Jerry Jones confirmed that Miller has signed, saying
the deal is contingent on Miller passing a physical, which he took
last night. The Cowboys probably will release rookie quarterback
Daniel Gonzalez to make room for Miller on the roster, Jones said.
</P>
<P>
   Agent Joe Linta said that the Cowboys called Monday to work out
the contract and that Miller is expected to join the team Tuesday.
Detroit released Miller two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
   The five-year veteran spent his first three seasons with
Pittsburgh when Cowboys head coach Chan Gailey was there. His
knowledge of Gailey's offense made him attractive to the Cowboys,
who said last week they would be re-evaluating the
third-quarterback job after the first game.
</P>
<P>
   Familiarity with the offense also swayed the deal for Miller,
who also drew interest from Chicago and Washington.
</P>
<P>
   ``He knows the system and with a few days of work could be ready
to play on Sunday,'' Linta said. ``It's the perfect place for
him.''
</P>
<P>
   The 6-foot-2, 210-pound Miller, who played at Michigan State,
has completed 45 of 81 passes for 520 yards with five interceptions
in his career. He has one career start.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
