<P>
   INTERNET-STOCKS (San Francisco) _ They're the Beanie Babies of
the stock market. Internet-based companies like Amazon.com,
GeoCities and Broadcast.com. mimic the little stuffed toys in a key
assumption: They make money now only because enough people agree
that they will be a valued collectible down the road. By MATT BEER.
