plunge last Monday with a sense of morbid curiosity. He wasn't
planning on cashing out his family's stock options any time soon,
but the prospect of figuring out how much they were worth on paper
wasn't quite as enticing as when the stock was climbing _ along
with their potential wealth. By VICTORIA COLLIVER.
