inevitably are trumpeted as ``blistering,'' ``scathing'' critiques
on the ills of bureaucracy _ be they redundant library branches,
overtime abuse or cockroaches in the jails. In the past year,
enterprising grand juries in Northern California have issued dozens
of detailed reports. At best, two-thirds of grand jury
recommendations are rejected or simply ignored. By VICKI HADDOCK.
