   FBN-ELWAY (Denver) _ All discussion of the Patriots' loss to the
Broncos must start and end with the fact that John Elway is still
at the top of the elite NFL quarterbacks. By Michael Madden.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS-COMMENT (Football Hades, Colo.) -- The numbers
might lead you to believe the Patriots came close to beating the
Broncos at Mile High Stadium for the first time since 1968 last
night. They did not. By Ron Borges.
</P>
<P>
   SOC-COLUMN (Undated) -- Rupert Murdoch makes it clear: He wants
to dominate world sport. By Frank Dell'Apa.
</P>
<P>
   RAC-COLUMN (Undated) _ Two-year-olds in Hopeful Stakes do
nothing to distinguish themselves. By Ron Indrisano.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
</P>
