<P>
   CLINTON-FLORIDA _ ORLANDO, Fla. _ In a calculated political
risk, Lt. Gov. Buddy MacKay prepares to host President Clinton in
two visits Wednesday at a time the president is under increasing
fire for his conduct in the Monica Lewinsky case. Clinton arrives
in Florida five days after Sen. Bob Graham said the Lewinsky affair
``will be an irreversible stain on the pages of his chapter in
history.'' MacKay lags behind Republican Jeb Bush in the polls and
hopes the president's visit will raise enough money to jumpstart
his campaign. (Crowley, Palm Beach Post) Eds: Will move late.
</P>
<P>
   POLMONEY-SENATE _ WASHINGTON _ With Majority Leader Trent Lott
having signaled that he will allow a Senate vote on campaign
finance reform, supporters began working out their strategy
Tuesday, including the timing of a vote and whether to offer it as
a separate bill or an amendment to appropriations legislation.
(Mollison, Cox News Service).
</P>
