<P>
   &UR; SPORTS EDITORS, NATIONAL EDITORS, PHOTO EDITORS: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times plans the following package of articles and
art when Mark McGwire breaks the home run record:
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MCGWIRE (St. Louis) _ Game story by Murray Chass.
</P>
<P>
   With two graphics: One, approximately 4 x 12, of McGwire's home
run history for season: where he hit them, off what pitcher, and
how far. A second, with assorted statistics related to his home
runs.
</P>
<P>
   With photos.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MCGWIRE-VESCEY-COLUMN (St. Louis) _ A Sports of The Times
column by George Vescey.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MCGWIRE-PROFILE (St. Louis) _ Man in the News feature. By
Jack Curry.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MCGWIRE-SCENE (St. Louis) _ The drama and the scene at the
ball park. By Jack Curry.
</P>
<P>
   Other stories as warranted.
</P>
<P>
   Of course there will be a second-day package of stories and
graphics, with reaction, appreciation and historical perspective.
</P>
