   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON _ WASHINGTON _ Amid mounting criticism from Congress,
President Clinton has invited Democrats to a White House meeting
Wednesday to discuss the Lewinsky scandal, to be followed by a
Thursday session with the bipartisan leadership. (Deans, Cox News
Service).
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-DELAY _ WASHINGTON _ As the House prepares whether to
consider impeachment of President Clinton, Majority Whip Tom DeLay,
R-Texas, has put together an elaborate team to provide members and
staff with information on every facet of the Clinton scandals.
(Harlan, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-FLORIDA _ ORLANDO, Fla. _ In a calculated political
risk, Lt. Gov. Buddy MacKay prepares to host President Clinton in
two visits Wednesday at a time the president is under increasing
fire for his conduct in the Monica Lewinsky case. Clinton arrives
in Florida five days after Sen. Bob Graham said the Lewinsky affair
``will be an irreversible stain on the pages of his chapter in
history.'' MacKay lags behind Republican Jeb Bush in the polls and
hopes the president's visit will raise enough money to jumpstart
his campaign. (Crowley, Palm Beach Post) Eds: Will move late.
</P>
<P>
   MCGWIRE-TAX _ WASHINGTON _ The IRS will issue a ruling exempting
any fan who returns slugger Mark McGwire's record 62nd home run
ball from federal gift taxes that could have approached $400,000,
the chairman of the Senate Finance Committee announced Tuesday.
(Glass, Cox News Service).
