the folks in this rural farming town think about the president and
his problems. (Foskett, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MEDICARE _ WASHINGTON _ The bipartisan Medicare commission got
an earful of suggestions Monday on how _ and how not _ to reform
the nation's health care system for the elderly. The commission
which is scheduled next March to recommend long-term revisions to
Medicare _ received confliction suggestions from a broad spectrum
of health care advocacy and interest groups over the wisdom of
issuing insurance vouchers, expanding managed care coverage and
providing long term care. (Lipman, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   POLMONEY-SENATE _ WASHINGTON _ With Majority Leader Trent Lott
having signaled that he will allow a Senate vote on campaign
finance reform, supporters began working out their strategy
Tuesday, including the timing of a vote and whether to offer it as
a separate bill or an amendment to appropriations legislation.
(Mollison, Cox News Service).
</P>
