<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Baseball pre-empts second part of ``Hill'' cliffhanger
 &HT;    By Bob Longino
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Propane may be big in Arlen, Texas, but it's not bigger than
Mark McGwire.
</P>
<P>
   Fans of Fox's animated ``King of the Hill'' will have to wait
until next Tuesday to watch the 'toon's season premiere _ and learn
who bites the dust in the propane explosion at fictitional Arlen's
Mega Lo Mart shown in last season's finale.
</P>
<P>
   Fox pre-empted Tuesday night's debuts of ``King'' and the new
sitcom ``Costello'' and a fresh episode of ``Guinness World
Records: Primetime'' to show the St. Louis Cardinals-Chicago Cubs
baseball game with home run sluggers McGwire and Sammy Sosa.
</P>
<P>
   ``King'' will now start its new season at 8 p.m. ET next
Tuesday. ``Costello'' will then air at 8:30 p.m., with ``Guinness''
at 9 p.m.
</P>
