   FBC-GATECH _ Improving the ACC's worst defense was the top
priority for Georgia Tech during the offseason and the Jackets
appeared to be headed in the right direction with the hiring of new
defensive coordinator Randy Edsall, who vowed to have the team use
a more aggressive, attacking style. But the new defensive strategy
backfired in last Saturday's 41-31 loss to Boston College, raising
many questions. (Rogers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 10 p.m.
ET
</P>
<P>
   FBC-UGA _ Lost in the excitement of Georgia's 56-3 victory over
Kent last week was the play of redshirt freshman defensive lineman
Josh Mallard, who had four sacks against the Golden Flashes. Such a
performance has been expected of Mallard, who dominated teammates
in preseason practice. A look at a player who could be one of the
team's surprises this season. (Schlabach, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 10 p.m. ET
</P>
<P>
   FBC-BACKUP-QBACKS _ Timing is everything in life, it's said, so
who are Matt Tittle, Patrick Fletcher and Eric Crouch to disagree?
For that matter, who are they, period? Before the football season,
they weren't exactly household names, except perhaps in their own
households. Before Saturday, September 5, they were seldom-used
backup quarterbacks and, for two of them, no change in that status
seemed in imminent. (Riggs, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-LONGHORNS _ UCLA, which plays for the first time this year
on Sept. 5 against No. 23 Texas, has a first-year defensive
coordinator, a new defensive scheme and plenty of questions.
``We'll go into the game not knowing how they'll line up,''
Longhorns Coach Mack Brown said. Unhappy with the Longhorns'
second-half ineffectiveness against New Mexico State in the season
opener, Brown and coordinator Carl Reese have shuffled the lineup.
(Wangrin, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
