</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Texas history buffs are worried that a Mexican
officer's myth-shattering account of Davy Crockett's capture and
execution after the battle of the Alamo may fall into the hands of
a dreaded Yankee. The diary, which has been privately owned by
Texans since 1974, will be auctioned Nov. 18 in California. It's
expected to fetch $250,000 to $300,000. By BARRY SHLACHTER. Story
has moved in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
