<P>
   AUSTIN _ As one indignant politician after another rose to
condemn President Clinton and the den of iniquity we have come to
know as the White House, I couldn't help but notice the dead
silence coming out of the Texas lieutenant governor's office. Not
that Bob Bullock would have any reason to offer _ or even be asked
_ about his views on Clinton's woes. I just couldn't help but think
that if anybody could empathize with Bill Clinton, it would be Bob
Bullock. By JAY ROOT. Story will move to Texas points in ``k''
commentary category. &QL; 
