<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Wednesday, Sept. 9 and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact Jeremy Bagott at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET-REBOUND (Los Angeles) -- What a difference a week makes.
Last week, the U.S. equity markets were in a tailspin following
news of a widening global meltdown, first in Asia, then Russia and
now Latin America. But on Friday, Fed chairman
</P>
<P>
   Alan Greenspan hinted that the central bank might ease interest
rates to protect the U.S. economy from the effects of a global
financial crisis. Investors held onto this hope, propelling the Dow
Jones industrial average to its highest one-day gain in history,
bolstering the broader market S&AMP;P 500 and Nasdaq composites. By
Deborah Adamson. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file only.)
</P>
<P>
   THQ-BASS-FISHING (Los Angeles) -- Just when you thought it was
safe to go back to arcade, Calabasas gamemaker THQ Inc. has
launched the first-ever 3D PC-based BASS fishing game. Yucks aside,
the BASS line is consistently one of the company's best-selling
titles. By Ben Sullivan. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news
file only.)
</P>
