<P>
   LA-SCHOOL-RETURN-EDUC (Los Angeles) _ As thousands of L.A.
Unified students return to classes today, many of them will be
learning in English for the first time. Others will be returning to
brand-new or reopened schools, and still others will face class in
schools torn up to make way for air conditioning that didn't arrive
on time. Temperatures are expected to be in the 90s. No other major
problems are reported. By Sherry Joe Crosby and Brooke Olson. (Will
move in the ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-BILINGUAL-EDUC (Los Angeles) _ The state's one-year English
immersion classes got a trial run a month ago, but today is the
biggest test of Proposition 227 as thousands of students return to
446 Los Angeles campuses and more around the state. By Yvette
Cabrera. (Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news
files.)
</P>
<P>
   SOFTBALL-ACLU (Los Angeles) _ The ACLU of Southern California
announced it is expanding its federal lawsuit against the city of
Los Angeles and its Parks and Recreation Department to include all
girls who want to participate in city-sponsored softball and
athletic programs. Last April, the group sued the city on behalf of
a girls' softball league that was being denied access to the same
fields that boys' leagues play on. By Alex Roth. (Will move in the
``n'' California, ``a'' national and ``s'' sports news files.)
</P>
<P>
   CA-CRIME-PLUNGE (Los Angeles) _ Crime rates throughout
California have plunged to their lowest levels since 1966,
according to a state report released Tuesday. The report shows a
statewide drop in each kind of violent crime, although in Los
Angeles the number of rapes increased 7 percent over the same time
last year. By David R. Baker. (Will move in the ``n'' California
and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-SHERIFF-APPOINT (Los Angeles) _ Sheriff Sherman Block
announced management changes in his department Tuesday, including
promoting Chief Rachel Burgess to acting assistant sheriff. By Doug
Haberman. (Will move in the ``n'' California news file.)
