   Soak it up, America: The mighty McGwire has gone deep one more
time.
</P>
<P>
   St. Louis Cardinals first baseman Mark McGwire ripped a fastball
over the left-field fence at Busch Stadium and became the
single-season home run leader, breaking Roger Maris' 37-year-old
record of 61 that most of the baseball world thought would never be
touched.
</P>
<P>
   The homer came off Chicago Cubs right-hander Steve Trachsel in
the fourth inning. It was measured at 341 feet, McGwire's shortest
of the season.
</P>
<P>
